    # Split the expression by '|'

    # Evaluate each part separated by '&'
    for part in or_parts:
        # Split by '&' and check if all are True ('t')
        and_parts = part.split('&')
        
        # If all parts of this 'and' segment are 't', the 'and' segment is True
        if all(p == 't' for p in and_parts):
            # If any 'and' segment is True, the entire expression is True
            return True
    
    # If none of the 'and' segments are True, the expression is False
    return False

def my_func(input1: str) -> bool:
    # Initialize the current result to None
    current_result = None
    # Initialize the last operator to None
    last_operator = None

    # Iterate through each character in the input string
    for char in input1:
        if char == 't':
            # True literal found
            bool_value = True
        elif char == 'f':
            # False literal found
            bool_value = False
        elif char in {'|', '&'}:
            # Operator found
            last_operator = char
            continue
        else:
            # In case of an invalid character
            raise ValueError("Invalid character in input string")

        if current_result is None:
            # Initialize the current result with the first boolean value
            current_result = bool_value
        else:
            # Apply the last operator found between the current result and the new boolean value
            if last_operator == '&':
                current_result = current_result and bool_value
            elif last_operator == '|':
                current_result = current_result or bool_value

    return current_result

# Testing the function with examples
print(my_func("f|t&f&f|f&f|f&f&t|t"))  # Expected: True
print(my_func("f&t|f&f"))  # Expected: False
print(my_func("t|t&f|t"))  # Expected: True

def my_func(expression: str) -> bool:
    # Split the expression by the OR operator '|'
    terms = expression.split('|')
    
    # Evaluate each term separately
    def evaluate_term(term):
        # Split the term by the AND operator '&'
        factors = term.split('&')
        # Evaluate each factor (which is either 't' or 'f')
        # Convert 't' to True and 'f' to False
        factors = [True if factor == 't' else False for factor in factors]
        # Return the result of ANDing all factors
        return all(factors)
    
    # Evaluate all terms and OR them together
    evaluated_terms = [evaluate_term(term) for term in terms]
    # Return the result of ORing all evaluated terms
    return any(evaluated_terms)

# Example usage
print(my_func("t|t&t|f"))  # Should return True
print(my_func("t&f|f|t|f&t|f&t&t&t|t|t|t|t&t&f|f&f|t&f"))  # Should return False
